31:53.654 --> 31:56.326
You let me know
if you remember anything else.

31:57.364 --> 31:58.361
Okay?

31:58.761 --> 32:00.099
Okay.

32:02.471 --> 32:03.771
What do we got, Rawls?

32:03.771 --> 32:05.431
Well,
I'm not entirely sure, sir.

32:05.431 --> 32:07.370
Don't suppose
you made these?

32:09.642 --> 32:10.976
Yeah.

32:10.976 --> 32:13.673
Uh, yeah,
all the time when I was a kid.

32:14.982 --> 32:16.945
There're boxes of 'em
in the garage.

32:16.945 --> 32:19.479
You know, it seems to me like
someone was squatting here
like this, and, you know,

32:19.479 --> 32:21.920
tossing them. Like so.

32:21.920 --> 32:23.320
Maybe drawin'
your son's attention?

32:24.019 --> 32:25.058
Look...

32:25.824 --> 32:27.124
Tell 'em I sent you.

32:27.124 --> 32:29.091
They'll rig your whole house
for a song.

32:29.091 --> 32:32.131
And mow your lawn,
for chrissake.

32:56.689 --> 32:57.486
Jakie.

33:26.388 --> 33:27.450
Holy shit.

33:32.187 --> 33:35.022
Daddy, look at this.

33:35.022 --> 33:36.525
Very cool, buddy.

33:36.525 --> 33:39.528
Hey, so, pile on the right
goes back on the shelves.

33:39.528 --> 33:42.362
Everything on the left,
we can bag and toss outside.

33:42.362 --> 33:44.231
This asshole
really did rob us,

33:44.231 --> 33:45.303
he needs a new line of work.

33:46.270 --> 33:47.437
Where the hell
did you find this?

33:49.670 --> 33:52.673
Uh, I've never seen that
before in my life.

33:52.673 --> 33:54.711
So, what's it doing in
the bottom of the wastebasket

33:54.711 --> 33:55.676
in my office?

33:56.483 --> 33:57.480
No idea.

33:58.553 --> 34:00.052
It's, uh...

34:00.052 --> 34:01.550
It's one of the first things
I ever carved.

34:04.824 --> 34:05.719
Lost it years ago.

34:07.622 --> 34:10.625
Speaking of things
carved out of wood...

34:12.929 --> 34:14.734
Can you...

34:14.734 --> 34:16.136
ditch this for me somewhere?

34:16.636 --> 34:18.202
What for?

34:18.202 --> 34:19.965
It's literally
his favorite thing in the world.

34:19.965 --> 34:21.936
Yeah, and you need to find him
a new favorite thing, my love.

34:21.936 --> 34:23.539
A quieter thing,

34:23.539 --> 34:25.373
'cause if he blows this shit
in my ear one more time,

34:25.373 --> 34:27.413
you are never
getting laid again.

34:27.413 --> 34:28.549
Okay.

34:28.549 --> 34:29.509
I'll hide it out here

34:29.509 --> 34:31.448
until he drives you nuts
asking for it.

34:31.915 --> 34:33.512
Thank you.

34:33.512 --> 34:35.485
Uh, garbage goes
out front tonight.

34:44.828 --> 34:46.861
<i>The score is now
two-zero in favor of Texas.</i>

34:46.861 --> 34:48.033
Fute.

34:48.033 --> 34:49.935
<i>- Anderson is trying...</i>
- Later, Jakie.

34:49.935 --> 34:51.899
- You can play Fute later.
- Fute.

34:51.899 --> 34:53.470
Fute.

34:54.475 --> 34:55.907
Fute!

34:55.907 --> 34:58.738
Okay. Okay, fine, I'll get it.

34:58.738 --> 35:00.840
But you better play quietly,
or Mommy'll kill me.

35:02.577 --> 35:03.783
Hey, what do you say
when I say,

35:03.783 --> 35:04.679
"if you're okay in the tub?"

35:05.816 --> 35:06.853
Fute.

35:06.853 --> 35:08.850
No, no. What do you say?

35:08.850 --> 35:10.050
"Okay."

35:10.050 --> 35:11.886
Okay. All right.

35:11.886 --> 35:14.388
Mommy and Auntie Anna
are across the hall
if you need 'em.

35:14.388 --> 35:16.122
I'm going downstairs
for a sec.

35:16.122 --> 35:17.858
Okay.

35:17.858 --> 35:21.229
Sis, I'm, like, juggling
four different campaigns.

35:21.229 --> 35:23.233
You know, you promised me rose

35:23.233 --> 35:24.998
- and <i>Real Housewives.</i>
- Are you okay?

35:24.998 --> 35:26.140
Okay!

35:35.551 --> 35:36.810
Is that Dolly?

35:37.818 --> 35:39.112
You okay up there?

35:39.112 --> 35:40.418
Okay!

35:48.025 --> 35:49.022
Huh.

35:49.022 --> 35:50.659
Dolly!

35:57.837 --> 35:59.565
You okay, Jake?

36:04.743 --> 36:05.674
Jake?

36:08.681 --> 36:09.678
Jake?

36:14.121 --> 36:16.151
What are you
supposed to say, Jake?

36:18.718 --> 36:20.359
Daddy asked you
a question, Jakie.

36:23.060 --> 36:24.360
Okay.

36:24.360 --> 36:25.994
Did you
turn the lights off?

36:25.994 --> 36:27.098
Nope.

36:27.098 --> 36:27.927
Who are you playing with?

36:30.299 --> 36:32.000
Oh. There he is.

36:32.000 --> 36:33.402
Dolly.

36:33.402 --> 36:35.041
Where'd I put it?

36:35.041 --> 36:36.202
Who are you
playing with?

36:36.202 --> 36:37.541
Dolly.

37:01.770 --> 37:02.797
The hell are you?

37:09.744 --> 37:11.905
Have you been
able to stop thinking
about what happened?

37:14.010 --> 37:14.809
No.

37:17.685 --> 37:18.747
Have you?

37:20.082 --> 37:20.881
No.

38:00.389 --> 38:01.394
<i>Patrick.</i>

38:03.896 --> 38:04.793
<i>Patrick.</i>

38:05.967 --> 38:06.795
Need to ask you a question.

38:08.068 --> 38:09.266
Harvey says he spotted you

38:09.266 --> 38:10.769
playing by the old
service steps.

38:10.769 --> 38:12.298
Yeah, because...

38:12.298 --> 38:14.803
I was just looking
for softer wood to carve
than all this stupid oak.

38:20.314 --> 38:22.712
All right.
Let's you and me take a walk.

38:23.816 --> 38:24.813
Come on.

38:40.564 --> 38:41.599
You gotta be shitting me.

38:56.181 --> 38:57.381
<i>Your Promethian</i>

38:57.381 --> 38:59.078
<i>Home Security System
is activated.</i>

39:14.366 --> 39:17.063
<i>The alarm system
will reset in 30 seconds.</i>

40:57.499 --> 40:58.703
Jesus.

41:28.398 --> 41:29.228
Oh, my God.

41:32.335 --> 41:33.705
Screw you.

41:54.461 --> 41:55.727
Come on,
you gotta be shitting me.

43:09.367 --> 43:10.164
Karina!

43:20.510 --> 43:22.110
Karina, wake up!

43:23.480 --> 43:24.744
Pat!

43:24.744 --> 43:26.779
Pat! What's going on?

43:26.779 --> 43:27.948
Did you see him?

43:27.948 --> 43:29.117
- Did you see him?
-See who?

43:29.517 --> 43:31.117
What?

43:31.117 --> 43:32.920
- Just go back inside, okay?
- No, but what...

43:32.920 --> 43:34.427
Just go back inside.
Lock the door.

43:34.427 --> 43:35.893
- Pat, what... No! Pat!
- Just stay here.

43:39.529 --> 43:40.997
Where are you?

43:42.136 --> 43:43.164
Are you in here?

43:44.633 --> 43:45.870
Where are you?

43:50.373 --> 43:51.205
Come on.

43:53.006 --> 43:54.648
Come on.

43:55.183 --> 43:56.210
It's me.

44:00.849 --> 44:01.780
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

44:01.780 --> 44:03.952
And nobody's here.

44:03.952 --> 44:05.285
I swear I saw something...

44:06.259 --> 44:07.555
Alarm.

44:07.555 --> 44:08.827
One sec.

44:11.892 --> 44:12.992
No fingerprints

44:12.992 --> 44:14.797
or any of the doors
or windows,

44:14.797 --> 44:16.596
and none of the molds
in the backyard

44:16.596 --> 44:18.870
came up a match.

44:18.870 --> 44:23.070
Power company did confirm
13 separate interruptions,

44:23.070 --> 44:25.673
but insist the problem
is not on their end.

44:25.673 --> 44:26.746
Meaning what?

44:29.112 --> 44:32.485
You haven't had a new face
show up, have you?

44:32.485 --> 44:34.386
Different guy
checkin' the gas meter,

44:34.386 --> 44:37.083
- or fixin' a cable?
- No.

44:37.083 --> 44:38.692
And nothing missing
from the house?

44:45.266 --> 44:46.931
Uh, Jake has this...

44:47.863 --> 44:50.832
musical instrument, um...

44:50.832 --> 44:53.135
a recorder
that he loves to play,

44:55.038 --> 44:58.074
which I might have
thrown out by mistake.

45:00.208 --> 45:01.680
But even if I did,
it would still be

45:01.680 --> 45:03.442
in one of the garbage cans,
which it's not.

45:08.286 --> 45:09.283
And I...

45:12.352 --> 45:15.058
I could have sworn
I heard it being played.

45:16.561 --> 45:17.929
You know, last night.

45:43.453 --> 45:45.019
Hey.

45:45.019 --> 45:46.826
Thought I said,
"Take some time off."

45:49.662 --> 45:51.094
I need to show you something.

45:58.601 --> 46:00.938
So, what?

46:00.938 --> 46:03.971
There's a thousand more
like it back at the house.

46:03.971 --> 46:05.273
That's the only owl
I ever made.

46:08.142 --> 46:10.278
Do you remember
where I lost it?

46:16.349 --> 46:17.824
Don't tell me
you went back there?

46:20.622 --> 46:22.288
No.

46:22.288 --> 46:25.293
I found it in a trash bin
at home yesterday.

46:26.565 --> 46:28.133
How is that possible?

46:28.133 --> 46:29.231
It's not.

46:31.035 --> 46:33.004
Look what else
I found in Mom's garage.

46:47.048 --> 46:48.250
What are you saying, Patty?

46:50.391 --> 46:51.825
You explain it. I...

46:53.553 --> 46:55.994
Mom always had a knack
for finding lost stuff.

46:56.661 --> 46:57.831
You know she did.

46:59.095 --> 47:00.460
Keep digging
through that house

47:00.460 --> 47:02.902
and I guarantee you'll find
all kinds'a crazy shit.

47:08.035 --> 47:09.403
Maybe, in the meantime,

47:12.010 --> 47:13.972
I think you should
give that shrink a call.

47:13.972 --> 47:15.343
What was her name?

47:17.349 --> 47:18.346
Mary?

47:18.845 --> 47:21.120
Barbara.

47:21.120 --> 47:24.317
Yeah, something's
been bubbling up in you
for a long time now,

47:24.317 --> 47:26.354
and she always seemed to help
back in the day.

47:49.149 --> 47:51.379
Yeah, let your
brother have a go, all right?

47:52.914 --> 47:53.953
Not too high.

47:55.555 --> 47:56.417
Are you serious?

48:00.659 --> 48:01.760
Gotta go.

48:01.760 --> 48:03.127
Push it back.
Push it back.

48:04.563 --> 48:05.393
Push it back.

48:10.131 --> 48:11.604
-Present.
- Jeez.

48:11.604 --> 48:13.401
- Jakie, you scared me.
- Present.

48:13.902 --> 48:15.538
It's from Dolly.

48:15.538 --> 48:16.437
What is this?

48:17.510 --> 48:18.406
It's a present.

48:19.642 --> 48:20.540
Okay?

48:21.314 --> 48:22.344
Okay.

48:38.861 --> 48:39.658
What the hell?

48:54.448 --> 48:55.943
Shit. Jakie.

48:55.943 --> 48:57.016
Jakie, come out of there!

48:57.680 --> 48:58.611
Jakie!

49:03.153 --> 49:03.950
Jakie.

49:06.956 --> 49:08.390
Get away from him!

49:09.224 --> 49:10.427
Get the hell away from my son!

49:10.427 --> 49:11.459
Jakie!

49:11.859 --> 49:13.230
Jakie!

49:15.665 --> 49:16.930
Jakie. Come here.

49:16.930 --> 49:18.631
Come here. Jakie.

49:19.669 --> 49:20.738
Jakie!

49:51.337 --> 49:55.668
What's happening
to you both is very normal.

49:55.668 --> 50:00.307
To have your home invaded
is a traumatic experience,

50:00.307 --> 50:03.646
one that brings up
all kinds of issues.

50:03.646 --> 50:04.578
Such as?

50:05.245 --> 50:06.646
Such as,

50:06.646 --> 50:10.221
"How will I ever let my son
out of my sight again?"

50:10.885 --> 50:12.485
Or...

50:12.485 --> 50:15.688
"Did I fulfill my obligation
as a husband

50:16.631 --> 50:20.062
"and a father, and a man,

50:20.062 --> 50:21.694
"to protect
my wife and child?"

50:23.198 --> 50:25.971
Karina, Pat's description.

50:25.971 --> 50:29.006
It's quite evocative
of a persistent phobia

50:29.006 --> 50:31.044
your husband
struggled with as a child.

50:33.042 --> 50:34.176
Which, of course,

50:34.176 --> 50:37.479
is how Pat and I
came to know each other.

50:41.723 --> 50:43.555
What phobia was that?

50:43.555 --> 50:44.552
<i>Patrick.</i>

50:45.789 --> 50:46.587
<i>Patrick.</i>

50:48.389 --> 50:49.557
<i>Let's you and me take a walk.</i>

50:50.661 --> 50:51.592
Come on.

50:55.069 --> 50:56.564
You know, long before
we built this yard,

50:57.737 --> 50:59.432
this whole forest

50:59.432 --> 51:01.404
was basically
one big copper mine.

51:03.771 --> 51:05.606
Kicked out half the product
for the entire state,

51:06.981 --> 51:08.741
before they finally
dug the sucker dry.

51:11.780 --> 51:13.718
This was how you got down
to the main entry shaft...

51:15.285 --> 51:17.321
...back when it was owned
by the mining company.

51:18.452 --> 51:19.587
Who owns it now?

51:20.823 --> 51:21.622
Us?

51:29.432 --> 51:31.368
Now it belongs to Bagman.

51:34.943 --> 51:36.736
-Who's Bagman?
- Shh!

51:40.608 --> 51:42.608
You never know
who might be listenin'.

51:42.608 --> 51:44.612
I told your brother this story
last summer,

51:44.612 --> 51:47.052
just like your granddad did me
when I was your age

51:47.052 --> 51:49.151
and his granddad's
granddad before that.

51:49.151 --> 51:51.454
And all of them
swore it was true.

51:53.290 --> 51:54.622
Just like
I'm swearing to you now.

51:56.564 --> 51:57.625
They say...

51:58.658 --> 52:00.562
he wanders
the world each night,

52:01.328 --> 52:02.428
searching for children

52:02.428 --> 52:04.632
to stuff in that
awful bag a' his.

52:05.799 --> 52:07.737
- Not just any children...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

52:07.737 --> 52:09.575
Let me guess.

52:09.575 --> 52:11.677
He wants the naughty children
that don't listen
to their parents or...

52:11.677 --> 52:13.575
Wrong, Patty.

52:14.848 --> 52:16.314
It's the good kids he wants.

52:17.347 --> 52:19.647
The shiny ones
and the dreamers.

52:21.154 --> 52:23.585
Once they catch his eye,
or grab his fancy,

52:24.519 --> 52:26.352
he won't rest
until he has them

52:26.352 --> 52:29.094
slung over his bony shoulder.

52:29.094 --> 52:31.494
Screamin' for help
that's never gonna come.

52:36.367 --> 52:37.564
No, you're just trying
to scare me...

52:37.564 --> 52:39.002
Damn right,
I'm trying to scare you, boy.

52:39.002 --> 52:40.237
<i>And scared you better be!</i>

52:40.237 --> 52:41.502
<i>Wander too close,
he'll drag you in</i>

52:41.502 --> 52:43.271
<i>and make pencils
out of your fingers,</i>

52:43.271 --> 52:44.705
and gobble
the rest of you down!

52:47.407 --> 52:48.676
Are you with me, boy?

52:52.520 --> 52:53.516
<i>Good.</i>

52:54.116 --> 52:55.188
Bagman?

53:21.374 --> 53:22.710
You drew these?

53:25.783 --> 53:26.714
Yep.

53:38.728 --> 53:40.728
That's what I meant
by a persistent phobia.

53:41.901 --> 53:43.632
Pat's was so intense,

53:44.665 --> 53:46.201
I felt it was crucial
to give him

53:46.201 --> 53:48.602
as much context as possible

53:48.602 --> 53:50.969
for the familial lore
that provoked it.

53:57.251 --> 54:02.286
As you can see,
the so-called Bag or Sackman,

54:02.286 --> 54:05.324
is a figure common
to almost every culture.

54:06.487 --> 54:09.228
Curiously, his methodology,

54:09.228 --> 54:11.759
even the phenomena
that accompany his presence,

54:12.493 --> 54:15.428
are remarkably consistent.

54:15.428 --> 54:17.695
He has the power to paralyze

54:17.695 --> 54:20.534
and incapacitate
parents and adults

54:20.534 --> 54:23.241
leaving their young ones
vulnerable.

54:23.241 --> 54:26.439
And he feeds off
the child's fear and anxiety.

54:26.439 --> 54:30.745
It sustains him, nourishes him.

54:30.745 --> 54:34.946
He can lure children to his lair
with toys or candy...

54:34.946 --> 54:38.421
And when the child
is at their most terrified,

54:38.421 --> 54:41.789
he steals them away
in his sack or bag.

54:42.856 --> 54:44.256
Are you trying
to make us feel stupid?

54:44.256 --> 54:45.759
On the contrary.

54:45.759 --> 54:49.928
I never told Karina
about the Bagman, Barbara,

54:49.928 --> 54:52.600
and it wasn't a dream
that broke into our house.

54:52.600 --> 54:56.173
No, but I'd suggest,
as a coping mechanism,

54:56.173 --> 54:58.744
you're projecting
the supernatural

54:58.744 --> 55:00.440
onto something...

55:00.440 --> 55:03.610
all too painfully real.

55:03.610 --> 55:07.016
And until you deal
with the real stuff

55:07.016 --> 55:08.387
bubbling up for you,

55:09.250 --> 55:10.684
the anger,

55:10.684 --> 55:14.587
the feelings of vulnerability,
and violation,

55:14.587 --> 55:17.026
your panic attacks
and nightmares

55:17.026 --> 55:18.661
will only get worse.

55:19.328 --> 55:20.531
Okay, so,

55:21.463 --> 55:22.830
what do you suggest we do?

55:27.367 --> 55:28.500
I see her.

55:28.500 --> 55:31.443
I'm the zombie.

55:32.707 --> 55:33.805
- Whoa! Hey, guys.
-Okay.

55:33.805 --> 55:35.643
So, he goes down 7:30
at the latest.

55:35.643 --> 55:37.442
- We read two stories...
- Two stories, yeah.

55:37.442 --> 55:38.983
...and then we sing
<i>Frere Jacques</i> when
he goes in the Pack 'n Play.

55:38.983 --> 55:40.685
Guys, check your phone.

55:40.685 --> 55:42.981
I just texted you
the confirmation number
for a room at the Hyatt.

55:42.981 --> 55:44.350
Two blocks from here,
three from the restaurant.

55:44.350 --> 55:45.952
Already paid for.

55:45.952 --> 55:47.724
Dinner's one thing,
but there's no chance in hell

55:47.724 --> 55:49.622
we're sleeping
in a different place
than Jakie right now.

55:49.622 --> 55:51.357
Who said anything
about sleeping?

55:51.357 --> 55:53.630
Who said sleeping?

55:54.895 --> 55:56.131
Will you just get her
out of here, Pat?

55:56.131 --> 55:57.731
Who said...

55:57.731 --> 56:00.037
Jakie,
listen to Auntie Anna, okay?

56:00.037 --> 56:01.206
Call any time!

56:01.206 --> 56:03.638
We can be back,
five minutes tops, okay?

56:03.638 --> 56:05.070
Gonna play zombie.

56:11.284 --> 56:12.880
I'm not sure
I'm up for this.

56:15.285 --> 56:16.455
Yeah, me neither.

56:19.120 --> 56:23.627
Worst case, we get dinner to go
and eat on Anna's couch.

56:25.162 --> 56:26.728
Yep.

56:26.728 --> 56:28.934
Let's at least try to make it
as far as dessert,

56:28.934 --> 56:29.963
so she can put Jakie down.

56:37.076 --> 56:37.905
So, what's the verdict?

56:41.982 --> 56:42.910
Is your husband nuts?

56:46.678 --> 56:47.915
Completely fricking crackers.

56:54.155 --> 56:57.430
So, what actually happened
with you and Liam at the mine?

56:59.633 --> 57:03.095
Well, I thought I felt someone
cut off a lock of my hair.

57:05.101 --> 57:05.933
I, uh...

57:07.501 --> 57:08.700
I lost my shit

57:08.700 --> 57:11.404
and then
we ran home screaming.

57:11.404 --> 57:13.575
A lock of your hair?

57:13.575 --> 57:16.380
Yeah. Bagman supposedly
always snips

57:16.380 --> 57:18.110
one off the kids
that catch his fancy.

57:19.019 --> 57:20.178
That's how it starts.

57:21.318 --> 57:22.147
What the hell for?

57:23.720 --> 57:25.917
So he always knows
where to find you.

57:25.917 --> 57:28.120
No matter where
you try to run or hide.

57:32.364 --> 57:35.128
Your father was something else.

57:35.128 --> 57:38.302
I think in his own way
he was just trying
to protect me.

57:38.302 --> 57:39.967
A cautionary tale
to keep me safe.

57:44.872 --> 57:46.475
All I remember
was Mom was furious

57:46.475 --> 57:48.311
'cause every night
I was convinced

57:48.311 --> 57:49.581
he was tapping on my window.

57:50.545 --> 57:52.613
And then one night,

57:52.613 --> 57:54.982
